FILE: Putco transports more than 210,000 passengers daily. (eNCA) JOHANNESBURG - The National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa says it feels vindicated. This after bus company Putco confirmed it won't be going ahead with retrenchments. The union held meetings with management, where it was confirmed that plans to retrench  214 employees have been cancelled. WATCH: COVID-19: Putco to retrench over 200 employees Job rotation will also stop on 15 March. Numsa says the company has been presented with alternatives. These include the employment of skilled artisans, instead of outsourcing maintenance work.